The course discusses the main events and key problems of international relations during the era of the Cold War. It analyses military strategy, ideology, propaganda and public diplomacy, diplomacy, summitry, the activities of special services, international organizations, European integration, main turning points in global politics and the development of international law.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective is to study the era of the Cold War in international relations, tracing the developments in military strategy, ideology and propaganda, diplomacy and secret services, European integration, international organisations and international law.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. The student knows the main events and turning points in the international history of the Cold War. 2. The student is able to characterize international relations in the Cold War era.
